SIMPLE: inconvenient
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inconvenient
<hw>In`con*ven"ient</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>inconveniens</ets> unbefitting: cf. F.
<ets>inconv⟦eacute⟧nient</ets>. See <er>In-</er> not, and
<er>Convenient</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Not becoming or suitable; unfit;
inexpedient.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not convenient; giving trouble, uneasiness, or
annoyance; hindering progress or success; uncomfortable;
disadvantageous; incommodious; inopportune; <as>as, an
<ex>inconvenient</ex> house, garment, arrangement, or
time</as>.</def></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Unsuitable; uncomfortable; disaccommodating;
awkward; annoying; unseasonable; inopportune; incommodious;
disadvantageous; troublesome; cumbersome; embarrassing;
objectionable.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inconveniently</ent>⟦br⟧
